https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/TLDP-brits@2000x1270-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/TLDP-brits@2000x1270-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/TLDP-brits@2000x1270-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/TLDP-brits@2000x1270-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/TLDP-brits@2000x1270-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p><a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/the-last-dinner-party">最后一个晚宴派对</a>昨晚（3月1日）获得了英国最佳新艺术家<a href="https://www.nme.com/tag/brit-awards">奖</a>，向英国的基层音乐场所大喊大叫。在下面查看他们的演讲。</p><ul><li><strong>阅读更多：<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/here-are-all-the-winners-from-the-brit-awards-2025-3842577">这是2025年英国奖的所有获奖者</a></strong></li></ul><p><a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-brits-announce-2024-rising-star-winner-3555457">在2024年获得《英国人的后起之秀》奖</a>后，伦敦乐队今年回到了最佳新艺术家，他们发行了首张专辑《 <a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/album/the-last-dinner-party-prelude-to-ecstasy-album-review-radar-3577784">Prelude to Ecstasy</a> 》。</p><p>在演讲中，他们花了一点时间来强调英国基层音乐场所面临的目前挑战。随之而来的是，有报道称， <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/grassroots-music-venues-uk-mvt-report-2024-closing-government-action-needed-kate-nash-parliament-3832257">2024年英国每两周失去一个基层音乐场所</a>- 近一半损失，在紧急状态中还剩下200个，因为该国面临“巡回演出崩溃”。</p><p>贝斯手佐治亚·戴维斯（Georgia Davies）说：“我们不会成为乐队，如果没有英国令人难以置信的独立场所，这里的许多艺术家也不是乐队，他们是音乐界的命脉，他们快要死了。”</p><p> “而且，如果这样的场所像O2，竞技场一样，该国的体育场为这些独立的场地贡献了一点，那么我们不会以这种令人震惊的速度失去它们。没有他们，我们不会在这里，没有他们，这一切都不会发生。</p><p>她继续说：“因此，我想对今晚在全国各地扮演独立场所的所有艺术家说，继续前进，因为那是最好的艺术。” “而且，在艺术受到威胁时，这是保持支持的最重要的事情。”您可以在下面观看他们的完整演讲。 </p><p><iframe loading="lazy" title="最后的晚宴大喊大叫独立场所，赢得了最佳新艺术家|英国奖2025" width="696" height="392" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/4BtjoUqOh80?feature=oembed&enablejsapi=1" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen></iframe></p><p>去年<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/government-back-arena-ticket-levy-to-save-grassroots-music-but-urgent-deadline-is-needed-to-prevent-an-even-gloomier-future-3812464">建议，在建议对体育场和竞技场演出的征费</a>之前<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-case-has-been-made-for-a-1-ticket-levy-on-all-arena-gigs-for-the-survival-of-grassroots-venues-and-artists-3611533">，政府的CMS选择委员会调查</a>后，音乐行业的上层梯队应该<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/industry-reacts-as-mps-recommend-ticket-levy-on-arenas-and-stadiums-to-save-grassroots-venues-and-artists-3755386">偿还基层和更广泛的生态系统的</a>想法。 A <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/uk-government-reveals-deadline-for-music-industry-to-respond-to-ticket-levy-to-save-the-grassroots-3820498">March deadline has been set</a> for voluntary action before the government step back in and investigates making it mandatory.</p><p> However, despite the likes of <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/coldplay-uk-tour-stadium-london-wembley-hull-music-venue-trust-tickets-3794308">Coldplay</a> , <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/sam-fender-announces-uk-european-people-watching-tour-buy-tickets-3803992">Sam Fender</a> and <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/katy-perry-announces-lifetimes-2025-uk-tour-donating-to-music-venue-trust-buy-tickets-3813601">Katy Perry</a> making major contributions of their own, the benefits of the levy may not be felt for some time – and <a href="https://www.musicvenuetrust.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/MVT_2024-Annual-Report.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener">a recent report from Music Venue Trust</a> shows that venues are not out of the woods yet.</p><p> Last year saw around one venue close every two weeks, with a near 20 per cent increase in “emergency cases” with 200 still on red alert for closure. The report also found that venues investing in sales of food, alcohol, merchandise and more to subsidise the live music they put on due to a number of financial strains – including energy bills – has increased by 440 per cent in recent years, and from £114,814,162 in 2023 to £162,067,095 last year.</p><p> As a result, the UK has seen a decrease in the total number of live music shows (down 8.3 per cent since 2023) accompanied by an even steeper decline in ticket revenues (down 13.5 per cent since 2023).</p><p> This also comes after <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/uk-government-price-cap-ticket-touts-secondary-dynamic-consultation-chris-bryant-interview-3827671">the government announced a price cap for the re-sale of touted tickets</a> and an investigation into the practice of dynamic pricing. Visit <a href="https://www.musicvenuetrust.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/MVT_2024-Annual-Report.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a> for Music Venue Trust&#39;s full 2024 report. </p><p><iframe loading="lazy" title="BRITs 2025: The Last Dinner Party talk new material and the importance of prioritising mental health" width="696" height="392" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/Bmu_40qcJxo?feature=oembed&enablejsapi=1" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen></iframe></p><p> Last year, The Last Dinner Party were forced to <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-last-dinner-party-cancel-european-tour-dates-burnout-3806400">cut their European tour short</a> citing “emotional, mental, physical burnout”. Several concerts on their <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-last-dinner-party-announce-uk-and-ireland-tour-dates-for-2024-buy-tickets-3578583">UK and Ireland tour</a> in <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-last-dinner-party-postpone-cardiff-show-due-to-illness-3798045">Cardiff,</a> Lincoln, Birmingham, Nottingham, Bristol and Southampton were also scrapped due to ill health.</p><p> In other news, the band has been confirmed to be opening for <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/olivia-rodrigo">Olivia Rodrigo</a> at her <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/olivia-rodrigo-announces-her-biggest-ever-uk-show-at-bst-hyde-park-2025-3811479">biggest ever UK show with a headline slot</a> at <a href="https://www.nme.com/festivals/british-summer-time-bst-festival">BST Hyde Park</a> 2025.</p><p> In a <a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/album/the-last-dinner-party-prelude-to-ecstasy-album-review-radar-3577784">four-star review of the band&#39;s critically acclaimed debut</a> , <em>NME</em> wrote: “Some may choose to posit the band&#39;s success as an antidote to the intense scrutiny – about their rise, appearance and decision to make music without a &#39;serious&#39; intention – they&#39;ve received in their early career. But take all of that away, and you&#39;re still left with fantastic songs that are easy to embrace and return to. It&#39;s hard to miss all the things they&#39;re doing right.”</p><p> The post <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-last-dinner-party-shout-out-grassroots-music-venues-as-they-win-best-new-artist-at-the-brit-awards-2025-3842703">The Last Dinner Party shout out grassroots music venues as they win Best New Artist at the BRIT Awards 2025</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
